dcterms:description: ARBORETUM is the largest publicly accessible dataset designed to advance AI for biodiversity applications, comprising over 134.6 million images across seven taxonomic classes, including Aves, Arachnida, Insecta, Plantae, Fungi, Mollusca, and Reptilia. Each image is annotated with scientific names, taxonomic details, and common names, making it a valuable resource for multimodal vision-language AI models.
dcterms:title: ARBORETUM

dcterms:description: ARBORETUM-40M is a subset of the ARBORETUM dataset, comprising approximately 40 million samples and 33K species, constructed to reduce skewness in species counts and facilitate balanced training.
dcterms:title: ARBORETUM-40M

dcterms:description: ARBORETUM-BALANCED is a curated dataset designed to enforce a balanced species distribution across the seven categories, with each category including up to 500 species and 50 images per species.
dcterms:title: ARBORETUM-BALANCED

dcterms:description: ARBORETUM-UNSEEN is a test dataset constructed to evaluate the generalization capability of models on unseen species, containing species with fewer than 30 instances in ARBORETUM.
dcterms:title: ARBORETUM-UNSEEN

dcterms:description: ARBORETUM-LIFESTAGES is a dataset focusing on recognizing species across various developmental stages, specifically for insects, containing images filtered by life stages such as egg, larva, pupa, or adult.
dcterms:title: ARBORETUM-LIFESTAGES
